<p>Because the value in a variable of an unsigned type can never be less than zero, testing to see if it is negative is a useless operation which can
only confuse future readers of the code.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
unsigned int i = 0; // the lowest value this var can have
...
if (i &gt;= 0) { // Noncompliant
  do_x(i);
}
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>
<pre>
unsigned int i = 0;
...
do_x(i);
</pre>